sentences.text:
In this case, the matters raised by the appellant, namely:

&#8226; the fact that Mr Shi signed the form in the context of an authority to act;

&#8226; the fact that the appellant had not notified Mr Shi of his new address; and

&#8226; the fact that Mr Shi failed to tell the appellant about the Tribunal hearing;

do not constitute fraud on the Tribunal within the meaning of SZFDE and there is not sufficient evidence to support such a conclusion.
